    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>B3 spectral observation of cyanoformaldehyde in SGR B2</prj:name>
        <prj:note>Cyanoformaldehyde (HCOCN) is an asymmetric top with dipole moment on the two principal axes. Around the star forming region, this molecule could be formed by the exo-thermic reaction between two abundant
interstellar species, H2CO and CN. Till date confirm detection of HCOCN have not been reported. The search for complex molecule get thrust after observation by new highly sensitive ALMA observatory is possible. With our chemical model, we have noticed that the column density of HCOCN molecule is significantly higher. Based on our quantum chemical calculation, we have predicted the rotational transitions of HCOCN molecule should be easily detected by ALMA. We are proposing to observe 115.2209974 GHz line frequency (3rd} band of ALMA) of the gas phase HCOCN molecule.</prj:note>
