        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We want to observe SGR B2 (RA: 17h47m20.4s, Dec: −28d23′07.08′′) in spectral line mode to search for cyanoformaldehyde. The central frequency of cyanoformaldehyde emission line is 115.2209974 GHz.
Since SGR B2 have source velocity of 61.6 km/s at a red shift of z = 0.000205497, the corresponding observing frequency will be 115.19733 GHz. We will use 3rd band with 58.594 MHz (152 km/s) bandwidth and 35.28 kHz (0.092 km/s) channel resolution.Since we opt for finest resolution bandwidth (35.28 kHz) for our observation and we want atleast 7 mJy sensitivity per pointing (which is equivalent to 0.403099K). By using ALMA time estimator,we find 2.71hr total on source time is required to achieve our intended sensitivity. We will also need 1.66h calibration time and 71.70m observation overhead. In addition, we will need additional 2.78h overhead for extra configuration. So, in total, we will need 22.26h observation time.
Since the size of SGR B2 is &gt; 4 arcmin, we will need complementary ACA observation to detect large scale structure of the source. We understand that full structure of SGR B2 will not be detected with single scan observation even if we observe with ACA but detection of structure of the order of 20 arcsec, which is detectable by ACA, will be sufficient for our scientific purpose.
</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
